.TH erl_parse 3 "stdlib 7.3" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
erl_parse \- This module is the basic Erlang parser that converts tokens into the abstract form of either forms (that is, top-level constructs), expressions, or terms.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The Abstract Format is described in the ERTS User's Guide. Notice that a token list must end with the dot token to be acceptable to the parse functions (see the \fIerl_scan\fR) module.

.SS "Error Information"

.PP
ErrorInfo is the standard ErrorInfo structure that is returned from all I/O modules. The format is as follows:

.IP
.nf
{ErrorLine, Module, ErrorDescriptor}

.fi

.PP
A string describing the error is obtained with the following call:

.IP
.nf
Module:format_error(ErrorDescriptor)

.fi

.SS "See Also"

.PP
\fIerl_anno\fR, \fIerl_scan\fR, \fIio\fR, section The Abstract Format in the ERTS User's Guide.

